&lt;div id=&#34;what-is-laravelhttpslaravelcomdocs10xmeet-laravel&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://laravel.com/docs/10.x#meet-laravel&#34;   target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;
    What is Laravel&lt;/a&gt; 
    &lt;span
        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100&#34;&gt;
        &lt;a class=&#34;group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700&#34;
            style=&#34;text-decoration-line: none !important;&#34; href=&#34;#what-is-laravelhttpslaravelcomdocs10xmeet-laravel&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;        
    
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Laravel is a web application framework with expressive, elegant syntax.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A web framework provides a structure and starting point for creating your application, allowing you to focus on creating something amazing while we sweat the details.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div id=&#34;what-is-vue-jshttpsvuejsorgguideintroductionhtml&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://vuejs.org/guide/introduction.html&#34;   target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;
    What is Vue js!&lt;/a&gt; 
    &lt;span
        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100&#34;&gt;
        &lt;a class=&#34;group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700&#34;
            style=&#34;text-decoration-line: none !important;&#34; href=&#34;#what-is-vue-jshttpsvuejsorgguideintroductionhtml&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;        
    
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Vue is a JavaScript framework for building user interfaces.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;It builds on top of standard HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;It Helps you efficiently develop user interfaces, be they simple or complex.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div id=&#34;what-is-vite-jshttpsvitejsdevguidewhyhtml&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://vitejs.dev/guide/why.html&#34;   target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;
    What is Vite js!&lt;/a&gt; 
    &lt;span
        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100&#34;&gt;
        &lt;a class=&#34;group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700&#34;
            style=&#34;text-decoration-line: none !important;&#34; href=&#34;#what-is-vite-jshttpsvitejsdevguidewhyhtml&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;        
    
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Vite is a build tool that aims to provide a faster and leaner development experience for modern web projects. It consists of two major parts:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A dev server that provides rich feature enhancements over native ES modules, for example extremely fast Hot Module Replacement (HMR).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A build command that bundles your code with Rollup, pre-configured to output highly optimized static assets for production.

  



